canonical:
  title: 宿龍潭驛
  author: 安軸
  language: lzh
  text: 寄宿茅茨下霜濃冽氣嚴困來伸病脚危坐撚踈髥屋老塵栖壁䆫明月掛簷心忙眠未穩斗覺夜厭厭
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 宿龍潭驛
  author: 安軸
  language: lzh
  text: 寄宿茅茨下。霜濃冽氣嚴。困來伸病脚。危坐撚踈髥。屋老塵栖壁。䆫明月掛簷。心忙眠未穩。斗覺夜厭厭。
korean:
  title: 숙 용담역
  author: 안축
  language: kor
  text: |-
    초가 밑을 찾아들어 하룻밤을 묵느라니
    서리가 짙고 추운 기운 엄하구나
    몹시 피곤하여 병든 다리 뻗쳤다가
    정좌하고 앉아서 성긴 수염을 꼬네
    집은 낡아빠져 벽에 먼지투성이
    창만은 원하니 달이 추녀에 걸렸네
    마음이 바빠서 잠 편히 못 드는데
    밤은 왜 이리도 긴고, 몹시 지루하구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0120_010_0810&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Night at Yongdam Station
  author: An Chuk
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I found shelter beneath a thatched roof for the night,
    Frost thick and bitter cold pressing down.
    Exhausted, I stretched my ailing legs,
    Then sat upright, twisting my sparse beard.

    The house decays, dust clings to every wall,
    Only the window shines—the moon hangs on the eaves.
    My mind churns restlessly, sleep won't come,
    And the night stretches on, weary and long.
  footnotes:
    - Yongdam Station (龍潭驛) was a waystation along a travel route in medieval Korea
    - An Chuk was a Goryeo scholar-official whose travel poetry often reflects the discomforts and contemplative moments of journeying
